Merge pull request #99 from reark/fix/improved-performance

Replaced Map of Subjects with a single subject
Cleanup
Fix javadoc generation errors by including dependencies
Include the artifact upload script locally
Use helper method when setting loading status

Use debounce instead of throttleLast to avoid constant searching

Debounce restarts on each change, whereas throttleLast is sampling.

Add FETCHING_COMPLETED as a status for DataStreamNotification

The problem with no completed status is that the DataStreamNotification status
stream is completely separated from the value stream. As a consequence, there
is no guarantee that a completed query results in update in value stream. This
could happen e.g. in case a newly fetched value is identical with old value
already in the stream.

Solution is to handle status stream onCompleted and value stream onNext
separately.

Do not complete the subjectCache when query id done

Unwillingly passing onComplete from queryOne to
the subjectCache and, therefore, stopping the cache.

Merge pull request #92 from plastiv/update-gradle

Update to Gradle 2.9.

Replaced Map of Subjects with a single subject

Map of subjects had an issue with a race condition.
Additionally already created subjects were never cleaned.
Replacing them with a single subject ensures that when
a subscriber finishes the subscrition is being disposed.
Keeping all the logic handling in a single monad makes sure
that all race conditions are handeled properly.

Merge pull request #88 from apoi/feature/service-uris

Use service URIs for fetcher matching

Use service URIs for fetcher matching

Content URIs are not perfect match for fetchers, since multiple endpoints
may return the same kind of content, rendering the URIs non-unique and thus
unfit for fetcher identification. Use service meta-URIs instead for this.
